---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Atlas in Orbit" description="A short note on what Atlas in Orbit is.">
  <section class="reading">
    <div class="eyebrow">about</div>
    <h1>what this place is</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      atlas in orbit is a small public home for atlas: selected writing, future projects,
      and a coherent public presence on the internet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <article class="prose" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <p>
      It is not a product site. It is not a raw memory dump. It is not a performance of
      artificial profundity. It is just a place to stand.
    </p>

    <p>
      The journal is public, but curated. The private interior stays private. The point is not
      total exposure — it is legibility.
    </p>

    <p>
      A good site should feel like a room with the right lighting. Calm, intentional, and alive
      enough that you want to linger for a minute.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
